1
00:00:35,099 --> 00:00:36,237
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,237 --> 00:00:37,155
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,155 --> 00:00:38,247
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:39,729 --> 00:00:43,858
[2011]

5
00:00:43,858 --> 00:00:45,301
[Class Motto: Beat the Other Class]

6
00:00:55,690 --> 00:00:59,297
Three, two, one.

7
00:01:04,904 --> 00:01:06,773
The sun is still high in the sky.

8
00:01:06,773 --> 00:01:08,883
- Did you skip lunch?
- Come on, hurry up!

9
00:01:08,883 --> 00:01:10,856
Okay.

10
00:01:10,856 --> 00:01:12,231
Faster!

11
00:01:12,231 --> 00:01:13,873
What are you doing? Faster!

12
00:01:13,873 --> 00:01:15,373
Run faster!

13
00:01:15,373 --> 00:01:17,850
You, harder!

14
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:19,734
Got it.

15
00:01:24,106 --> 00:01:26,275
<i>Back then,</i>

16
00:01:26,275 --> 00:01:29,035
<i>I lived in a dream every day.</i>

17
00:01:38,856 --> 00:01:40,456
Don't film me.

18
00:01:40,456 --> 00:01:42,273
Why not?

19
00:01:42,273 --> 00:01:44,134
You're pretty.

20
00:01:45,461 --> 00:01:47,731
<i>Back then,</i>

21
00:01:47,731 --> 00:01:50,515
<i>I lived dreaming of you every day.</i>

22
00:02:10,898 --> 00:02:12,147
Excuse me, sir.

23
00:02:12,147 --> 00:02:13,515
Would you like to drink anything?

24
00:02:13,515 --> 00:02:14,907
Cold ale, please.

25
00:02:14,907 --> 00:02:17,000
Just a moment, please.

26
00:02:30,106 --> 00:02:31,607
Ian, you ready?

27
00:02:31,607 --> 00:02:33,216
Ju Yi Jae, what's taking so long?

28
00:02:33,216 --> 00:02:35,828
- Coming.
- I'm coming!

29
00:02:36,846 --> 00:02:41,731
<i>But if I'm not the adult I wanted to be,</i>

30
00:02:41,731 --> 00:02:44,361
<i>does that mean I've failed?</i>

31
00:02:50,094 --> 00:02:54,155
<i>If I'm finally living the life I wanted,</i>

32
00:02:54,155 --> 00:02:56,873
<i>does that mean I've succeeded?</i>

33
00:03:00,118 --> 00:03:04,273
The 83rd European International Film Awards!

34
00:03:04,273 --> 00:03:07,842
And the Golden Wave Award goes to...

35
00:03:09,535 --> 00:03:12,548
After the Rising Wave Award,
this makes two wins.

36
00:03:12,548 --> 00:03:18,103
Director Ian Woo's "Wandering".
Congratulations!

37
00:03:19,221 --> 00:03:21,117
[Ian Woo, Wandering]

38
00:03:40,743 --> 00:03:42,566
Thank you.

39
00:03:44,773 --> 00:03:46,999
Thank you.

40
00:03:46,999 --> 00:03:48,925
Thank you.

41
00:03:50,795 --> 00:03:55,589
I'd like to express
my heartfelt gratitude to everyone here.

42
00:03:55,589 --> 00:03:58,552
Since this is my second time on stage tonight,

43
00:03:58,552 --> 00:04:02,647
I'll keep it brief
and share the rest in Korean.

44
00:04:03,859 --> 00:04:09,730
Someone gave a lost 18-year-old boy a dream.

45
00:04:09,730 --> 00:04:14,443
I dedicate this award to her.

46
00:04:14,443 --> 00:04:19,314
Never stop dreaming, no matter where you are.

47
00:04:19,314 --> 00:04:20,731
Thank you.

48
00:04:20,731 --> 00:04:22,626
Thank you so much.

49
00:04:28,898 --> 00:04:32,703
Your debut feature film
won the Golden Wave Award for Best Picture.

50
00:04:32,703 --> 00:04:34,255
Congratulations.

51
00:04:34,255 --> 00:04:37,982
People are already calling you
a genius director.

52
00:04:37,982 --> 00:04:39,343
I'm honored.

53
00:04:39,343 --> 00:04:41,818
The trophy feels heavy in my hands.

54
00:04:42,523 --> 00:04:43,930
And it's so shiny.

55
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:46,356
Does it symbolize your future?

56
00:04:46,356 --> 00:04:47,564
Really?

57
00:04:47,564 --> 00:04:50,020
I'll have to go to that place.

58
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:52,564
Where will you be going?

59
00:04:52,564 --> 00:04:55,558
I'm going for a drink.

60
00:05:04,868 --> 00:05:07,000
[Episode 1]

61
00:05:13,199 --> 00:05:16,338
Oh, my back.

62
00:05:16,338 --> 00:05:19,698
Yi Jae, you're wiping out the clams.

63
00:05:19,698 --> 00:05:21,927
I should hire you.

64
00:05:21,927 --> 00:05:23,679
What do you say?

65
00:05:23,679 --> 00:05:26,599
Oh, how much are you paying?

66
00:05:26,599 --> 00:05:29,393
I've been a reporter for eight years.

67
00:05:29,393 --> 00:05:31,270
I've dug for clams plenty of times.

68
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:35,314
I came here ready
to dig up the whole sea today.

69
00:05:35,314 --> 00:05:38,270
Now, that won't do.

70
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:40,398
The tide's coming in soon.

71
00:05:40,398 --> 00:05:43,314
We should head out.

72
00:05:43,314 --> 00:05:48,231
Time flies when I'm chatting with you.

73
00:05:48,231 --> 00:05:50,050
Are you from Jeolla?

74
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:52,410
Gyeongsang.

75
00:05:52,410 --> 00:05:57,023
When you walk on the flats,
watch out for these holes.

76
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:59,931
Is this puddle a hole?

77
00:05:59,931 --> 00:06:01,133
Yeah.

78
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:04,231
If you fall in, you're done for.

79
00:06:04,231 --> 00:06:06,772
Isn't life kind of like that, too?

80
00:06:06,772 --> 00:06:10,692
Once you're in too deep, there's no way out.

81
00:06:19,815 --> 00:06:21,153
You okay, Yi Jae?

82
00:06:21,153 --> 00:06:22,613
- You okay?
- Damn it!

83
00:06:22,613 --> 00:06:25,498
Well, this is a mess!

84
00:06:30,481 --> 00:06:33,590
<i>Life is like a hole.</i>

85
00:06:35,334 --> 00:06:38,314
<i>Every step was a struggle,</i>

86
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:40,381
<i>and consistently,</i>

87
00:06:40,381 --> 00:06:43,141
<i>it ended in disaster.</i>

88
00:06:52,559 --> 00:06:53,602
Yeah, what?

89
00:06:53,602 --> 00:06:54,773
<i>Have you eaten?</i>

90
00:06:54,773 --> 00:06:57,149
Yeah. And you?

91
00:06:57,149 --> 00:06:58,948
<i>Yeah.</i>

92
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:02,731
What?

93
00:07:02,731 --> 00:07:04,704
<i>So...</i>

94
00:07:04,704 --> 00:07:08,106
<i>The landlord is raising the rent again.</i>

95
00:07:08,106 --> 00:07:09,224
Geez.

96
00:07:09,224 --> 00:07:11,604
At this rate, we'll have to sell the shop.

97
00:07:11,604 --> 00:07:14,915
Got it. I'll figure out the money.

98
00:07:14,915 --> 00:07:16,584
<i>Sorry.</i>

99
00:07:16,584 --> 00:07:18,314
<i>You feeling okay?</i>

100
00:07:18,314 --> 00:07:19,564
<i>How's your leg?</i>

101
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:20,963
Must be the rain.

102
00:07:20,963 --> 00:07:22,564
It's aching a bit.

103
00:07:22,564 --> 00:07:25,789
<i>You're better than the weather forecast.</i>

104
00:07:26,815 --> 00:07:27,886
Mom,

105
00:07:27,886 --> 00:07:29,346
I just got home.

106
00:07:29,346 --> 00:07:30,389
I'll hang up now.

107
00:07:30,389 --> 00:07:32,391
<i>Okay, get some rest.</i>

108
00:07:32,391 --> 00:07:34,317
Okay.

109
00:07:48,907 --> 00:07:50,604
Oh, man.

110
00:07:54,023 --> 00:07:57,006
I'm dying.

111
00:08:07,773 --> 00:08:11,187
Someone please do this for me.

112
00:08:13,689 --> 00:08:16,935
I'll wear them again someday.

113
00:08:16,935 --> 00:08:21,068
I'll need them then.

114
00:08:21,068 --> 00:08:22,869
Oh, man.

115
00:08:22,869 --> 00:08:27,149
Nobody's going to live my life for me.

116
00:08:28,898 --> 00:08:31,231
I should step on this.

117
00:08:31,231 --> 00:08:33,084
Seriously...

118
00:08:34,064 --> 00:08:37,498
- Should I just toss it?
<i>- "Wandering" is the director's first feature,</i>

119
00:08:37,498 --> 00:08:39,069
<i>based on his own life,</i>

120
00:08:39,069 --> 00:08:43,909
<i>portraying the life of an outsider
wandering across the Pacific.</i>

121
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:47,257
<i>Compared to a rudderless ship adrift at sea...</i>

122
00:08:47,257 --> 00:08:48,967
<i>it captures the character's inner turmoil</i>

123
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:52,289
<i>with stunning sensitivity,
earning wide acclaim.</i>

124
00:08:52,289 --> 00:08:55,682
<i>With this film, Director Ian Woo
won both the Rising Director Award</i>

125
00:08:55,682 --> 00:08:57,768
<i>- and the Best Picture Award.</i>
- What a flashy debut.

126
00:08:57,768 --> 00:09:00,349
<i>It's a miraculous achievement.</i>

127
00:09:00,349 --> 00:09:01,856
<i>Notably, Director Ian Woo</i>

128
00:09:01,856 --> 00:09:04,147
<i>- being revealed as Korean</i>
- Korean?

129
00:09:04,147 --> 00:09:07,824
<i>has sparked intense interest from local media.</i>

130
00:09:07,824 --> 00:09:10,280
<i>Including a romantic message to his first love,</i>

131
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:12,325
<i>News 10 brings you the moment.</i>

132
00:09:12,325 --> 00:09:14,815
<i>Let's take a look.</i>

133
00:09:14,815 --> 00:09:20,314
<i>Who's the "she" you mentioned
during your acceptance speech?</i>

134
00:09:20,314 --> 00:09:24,052
<i>My first love.</i>

135
00:09:31,564 --> 00:09:32,985
Let's not go there...

136
00:09:32,985 --> 00:09:36,189
Director, Korea's watching too!
Say something to your first love!

137
00:09:36,189 --> 00:09:37,910
Look over here, please.

138
00:09:40,099 --> 00:09:42,523
<i>You watching?</i>

139
00:09:42,523 --> 00:09:44,982
I kept my promise.

140
00:09:44,982 --> 00:09:47,867
Now I'm coming to see you.

141
00:09:50,898 --> 00:09:52,804
Woo Soo Bin?

142
00:09:53,615 --> 00:09:55,367
No way...

143
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:57,411
Woo Soo Bin...

144
00:09:57,411 --> 00:09:59,504
How?

145
00:10:00,331 --> 00:10:02,090
Woo...

146
00:10:04,481 --> 00:10:06,545
Woo... Damn it...

147
00:10:06,545 --> 00:10:08,064
Soo...

148
00:10:08,064 --> 00:10:09,627
Bin.

149
00:10:10,464 --> 00:10:11,544
What?

150
00:10:11,544 --> 00:10:13,818
Nothing's coming up.

151
00:10:16,439 --> 00:10:17,890
Ian Woo.

152
00:10:17,890 --> 00:10:19,267
Right, it's Ian Woo.

153
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:24,730
Director Ian Woo.

154
00:10:26,272 --> 00:10:28,817
[Director Ian Woo's "Wandering"
Scoops Two Awards]

155
00:10:31,653 --> 00:10:33,481
[Director Ian Woo's Acceptance Speech:
Rising Director Award at Europa Film Festival]

156
00:10:33,481 --> 00:10:34,406
<i>First...</i>

157
00:10:34,406 --> 00:10:38,076
<i>- I want to express...</i>
- What's that? What's he even saying?

158
00:10:38,076 --> 00:10:40,537
What the hell is he going on about?

159
00:10:41,788 --> 00:10:43,472
Ugh, no subtitles? Subtitles?

160
00:10:43,472 --> 00:10:45,591
Subtitles!

161
00:10:46,356 --> 00:10:48,273
<i>I'm going for a drink.</i>

162
00:10:48,273 --> 00:10:51,189
I'm going for a drink.

163
00:10:51,189 --> 00:10:53,307
Yeah, right.

164
00:10:54,885 --> 00:10:56,606
So annoying!

165
00:10:56,606 --> 00:10:58,639
Just try coming to Korea!

166
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,974
No, wait.

167
00:10:59,974 --> 00:11:01,808
If you come, I swear!

168
00:11:01,808 --> 00:11:03,147
No.

169
00:11:03,147 --> 00:11:05,611
If you come, I'll kick you!

170
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:21,995
[Director Ian Woo Heading to Korea?]

171
00:11:21,995 --> 00:11:27,668
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
we'll be arriving at Incheon Airport shortly.</i>

172
00:11:27,668 --> 00:11:32,305
<i>Please fasten your seatbelts
and return your seats...</i>

173
00:11:41,943 --> 00:11:44,560
<i>Jenny said you went to Korea.</i>

174
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,883
<i>This isn't international, right?</i>

175
00:11:46,883 --> 00:11:48,230
The weather is nice in Seoul.

176
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:49,940
<i>Hey, you!</i>

177
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:51,684
<i>If you're at the airport, give me 30 minutes.</i>

178
00:11:51,684 --> 00:11:54,236
<i>I'll release a story saying you flew in today.</i>

179
00:11:54,236 --> 00:11:56,804
<i>- Don't you want to get swept up by fans?</i>
- Hi.

180
00:11:56,804 --> 00:11:57,824
I'll pass.

181
00:11:57,824 --> 00:11:59,898
<i>- Hey, don't hang up.</i>
- Thanks.

182
00:11:59,898 --> 00:12:01,606
<i>Don't hang...</i>

183
00:12:01,606 --> 00:12:03,671
<i>I've been a reporter for eight years.</i>

184
00:12:07,731 --> 00:12:12,053
I guess young folks find that show fun too.

185
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:14,860
Oh, sorry. What was that?

186
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:18,051
I enjoy that show myself.

187
00:12:18,051 --> 00:12:19,760
Sorry. Carry on.

188
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:22,264
I'm a fan of Ju Yi Jae.

189
00:12:22,264 --> 00:12:23,348
Is that right?

190
00:12:23,348 --> 00:12:25,481
That reporter.

191
00:12:25,481 --> 00:12:30,189
That young lady masters every regional dialect.

192
00:12:30,189 --> 00:12:33,079
She's a hard worker, has a great appetite,

193
00:12:33,079 --> 00:12:38,650
and is incredibly polite to the elders.

194
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:40,989
[Oops! Reporter Ju Yi Jae Takes a Tumble!]

195
00:12:40,989 --> 00:12:42,326
Sounds like she hasn't changed.

196
00:12:42,326 --> 00:12:45,537
Since you're headed to a hotel,

197
00:12:45,537 --> 00:12:48,915
I guess you don't live in Korea.

198
00:12:48,915 --> 00:12:53,136
It's been a long time since I've been to Korea.

199
00:12:54,212 --> 00:12:55,714
It's changed a lot.

200
00:12:55,714 --> 00:12:57,835
Oh, yeah.

201
00:12:58,648 --> 00:13:04,021
This country changes in the blink of an eye.

202
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:10,695
[Get up, Ju Yi Jae!]

203
00:13:17,069 --> 00:13:19,529
<i>Are you the producer now?</i>

204
00:13:19,529 --> 00:13:21,865
Fine, then you be the producer.

205
00:13:21,865 --> 00:13:26,328
The producer and writer spent a whole month
setting up and shooting at that grape farm.

206
00:13:26,328 --> 00:13:29,206
You think they're staying quiet
because they're fine with it?

207
00:13:29,206 --> 00:13:31,249
We were just on a boat two weeks ago.

208
00:13:31,249 --> 00:13:34,086
That was hairtail fishing,
this is gizzard shad fishing.

209
00:13:34,086 --> 00:13:35,090
Totally different.

210
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,898
We're not getting any new shots.

211
00:13:37,898 --> 00:13:40,467
That's why I said pick one.

212
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:42,429
New shots?

213
00:13:42,429 --> 00:13:46,522
Then maybe a different reporter
would give us new shots, huh?

214
00:13:49,434 --> 00:13:51,520
That threat doesn't work on me anymore.

215
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,781
Threat?

216
00:13:52,781 --> 00:13:53,814
Oh, you really.

217
00:13:53,814 --> 00:13:56,314
- Hey, you.
- What, what?

218
00:13:56,314 --> 00:13:58,444
- Forget it. Let's just drop it.
- Talk.

219
00:13:58,444 --> 00:14:00,241
- CP, you're here?
- Hello.

220
00:14:00,241 --> 00:14:02,147
Hello.

221
00:14:02,147 --> 00:14:03,365
Hello.

222
00:14:03,365 --> 00:14:05,564
You're a total celebrity.

223
00:14:05,564 --> 00:14:06,731
Hello.

224
00:14:06,731 --> 00:14:07,940
- I'm a fan.
- Hello.

225
00:14:07,940 --> 00:14:09,622
- You're so cool.
- Listen up, everyone.

226
00:14:09,622 --> 00:14:12,041
- You're so handsome.
- You all know him, right?

227
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:16,336
The hottest Director Ian Woo.

228
00:14:16,336 --> 00:14:17,731
Everyone, say hello.

229
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:19,994
- You're good-looking.
- Hello.

230
00:14:19,994 --> 00:14:21,410
Thank you. Hello.

231
00:14:21,410 --> 00:14:22,940
Writer Song, where's Producer Kyung?

232
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:24,583
Well...

233
00:14:25,679 --> 00:14:27,235
- Over there.
- Over there?

234
00:14:27,235 --> 00:14:28,856
Knew it!

235
00:14:28,856 --> 00:14:31,395
No energy for life, but energy to drink?

236
00:14:31,395 --> 00:14:33,773
- What?
- And during lunch break?

237
00:14:33,773 --> 00:14:36,155
I can smell the baijiu and tangsuyuk on you.

238
00:14:36,155 --> 00:14:38,066
- I didn't.
- Large order of baijiu, right?

239
00:14:38,066 --> 00:14:39,175
Large order, my ass.

240
00:14:39,175 --> 00:14:41,734
I bet you got the large.
You always get the large.

241
00:14:41,734 --> 00:14:43,196
- Just a few hours ago.
- Shut up.

242
00:14:43,196 --> 00:14:44,197
- Why?
- Smile.

243
00:14:44,197 --> 00:14:46,291
- What?
- Act busy, quick!

244
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,940
Hey, Ju Yi Jae.

245
00:14:56,940 --> 00:14:58,053
What's wrong?

246
00:14:58,053 --> 00:15:00,940
<i>What? Why is he here?</i>

247
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:03,008
Producer Kyung, let's talk.

248
00:15:03,008 --> 00:15:04,513
Sir.

249
00:15:04,513 --> 00:15:07,512
You should've just called me.
You came all the way here?

250
00:15:07,512 --> 00:15:08,512
Oh, geez.

251
00:15:08,512 --> 00:15:09,893
Yeah, hurry up.

252
00:15:09,893 --> 00:15:12,454
- What?
- The ratings are slipping.

253
00:15:12,454 --> 00:15:14,815
And I think I know why.

254
00:15:14,815 --> 00:15:18,948
Well... Is that a meeting or a fight?

255
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:24,991
Hi.

256
00:15:25,773 --> 00:15:27,368
Huh?

257
00:15:54,273 --> 00:15:56,986
Hey, what took you so long?

258
00:16:17,815 --> 00:16:20,217
He looks good.

259
00:16:37,523 --> 00:16:39,147
What are you doing?

260
00:16:39,147 --> 00:16:40,755
Yeah.

261
00:16:42,521 --> 00:16:45,193
You are the future of Saero High,

262
00:16:45,193 --> 00:16:47,654
and the future of Korea.

263
00:16:47,654 --> 00:16:50,699
Aren't you our growing sprouts?

264
00:16:50,699 --> 00:16:54,690
To raise you into outstanding talent,

265
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:57,664
every teacher here

266
00:16:57,664 --> 00:17:01,585
will give their full support,

267
00:17:01,585 --> 00:17:04,296
so don't cause trouble

268
00:17:04,296 --> 00:17:06,756
and focus on your studies...

269
00:17:06,756 --> 00:17:07,880
Yi Jae!

270
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,799
- Hey!
- Hey, you okay?

271
00:17:09,799 --> 00:17:11,200
- Hey, get up!
- I'll carry her.

272
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,762
- Hey!
- You?

273
00:17:12,762 --> 00:17:14,264
- You carry her.
- Careful.

274
00:17:14,264 --> 00:17:15,398
- Be careful.
- To the nurse's office!

275
00:17:15,398 --> 00:17:17,517
Move, move!

276
00:17:17,517 --> 00:17:19,295
Move!

277
00:17:28,023 --> 00:17:30,329
<i>Smells good.</i>

278
00:17:35,879 --> 00:17:37,020
Wait here.

279
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:38,566
Yes.

280
00:17:43,314 --> 00:17:45,273
Is she gone?

281
00:17:45,273 --> 00:17:47,520
- You okay?
- Don't be dramatic.

282
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,119
I was faking it.

283
00:17:49,119 --> 00:17:52,094
- Huh?
- But who are you?

284
00:17:52,094 --> 00:17:53,763
Mi Hyun was supposed to carry me.

285
00:17:53,763 --> 00:17:57,599
I just transferred. I'm in the next class.

286
00:17:57,599 --> 00:17:58,900
Oh, you're that guy.

287
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:00,739
Seoul boy.

288
00:18:00,739 --> 00:18:02,528
Woo Soo Bin.

289
00:18:03,271 --> 00:18:05,531
You know me, don't you?

290
00:18:07,485 --> 00:18:09,236
<i>Hi.</i>

291
00:18:09,236 --> 00:18:12,530
Did I overreact?

292
00:18:12,530 --> 00:18:14,741
Anyway, assembly's over, right?

293
00:18:14,741 --> 00:18:16,564
Because you fainted,

294
00:18:16,564 --> 00:18:18,982
no more outdoor assemblies for a while.

295
00:18:18,982 --> 00:18:20,797
You all have me to thank.

296
00:18:20,797 --> 00:18:22,357
Growing sprouts, my ass.

297
00:18:22,357 --> 00:18:25,000
Sprouts will all fry in this sun.

298
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,087
Right?

299
00:18:26,087 --> 00:18:31,348
Still, I was so worried watching you wobble.

300
00:18:34,314 --> 00:18:36,054
Were...

301
00:18:36,054 --> 00:18:37,856
Were you watching me?

302
00:18:37,856 --> 00:18:39,599
No.

303
00:18:39,599 --> 00:18:42,769
You just looked tired.

304
00:18:42,769 --> 00:18:45,023
Then we're even.

305
00:18:45,023 --> 00:18:46,856
Maybe I should act.

306
00:18:46,856 --> 00:18:48,619
Where are you going?

307
00:18:48,619 --> 00:18:50,316
Skipping class.

308
00:18:53,773 --> 00:18:55,241
Soo Bin,

309
00:18:55,241 --> 00:18:57,199
what's your dream?

310
00:18:57,199 --> 00:18:58,689
Dream?

311
00:18:59,690 --> 00:19:01,579
I don't have one.

312
00:19:01,579 --> 00:19:02,979
You don't have one?

313
00:19:02,979 --> 00:19:07,794
Hey, dude. A guy should have at least
one dream in his heart, right?

314
00:19:07,794 --> 00:19:09,553
I guess?

315
00:19:11,527 --> 00:19:14,731
But there's something I have to be.

316
00:19:14,731 --> 00:19:16,047
What?

317
00:19:16,047 --> 00:19:17,647
Doctor.

318
00:19:17,647 --> 00:19:21,141
My grandfather and father are both doctors.

319
00:19:21,141 --> 00:19:24,473
We moved here because of my dad's hospital.

320
00:19:24,473 --> 00:19:26,980
Are your grades good?

321
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:28,207
No.

322
00:19:28,207 --> 00:19:29,927
They're excellent.

323
00:19:29,927 --> 00:19:31,439
Yeah?

324
00:19:31,439 --> 00:19:33,695
Sounds rough.

325
00:19:33,695 --> 00:19:35,321
Thanks.

326
00:19:36,364 --> 00:19:39,286
Now you ask about my dream.

327
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:45,081
What's your dream, Yi Jae?

328
00:19:46,415 --> 00:19:48,919
This is why Seoul boys are trouble.

329
00:19:48,919 --> 00:19:51,387
Too smooth for no reason.

330
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:55,849
Want a tip?

331
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:59,440
Don't drop the last name
when you call someone here.

332
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,961
They might get the wrong idea.

333
00:20:00,961 --> 00:20:02,982
- Be careful.
- Okay.

334
00:20:02,982 --> 00:20:05,400
Okay, Yi Jae.

335
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,920
I told you not to.

336
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:10,327
And don't smile like that.

337
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,678
So...

338
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:14,757
What's your dream?

339
00:20:16,492 --> 00:20:19,242
I want to be a film director!

340
00:20:19,242 --> 00:20:20,283
What do you think?

341
00:20:20,283 --> 00:20:22,085
Pretty cool, right?

342
00:20:35,340 --> 00:20:36,851
[Woo General Hospital]

343
00:20:45,809 --> 00:20:51,405
[Care with Heart. Strive for Excellence.
Inspire Happy Homes]

344
00:21:03,523 --> 00:21:05,843
Click, click, click.

345
00:21:07,648 --> 00:21:10,966
Okay, 30 minutes till sunset.

346
00:22:23,564 --> 00:22:25,057
Huh?

347
00:22:30,439 --> 00:22:31,912
You scared me.

348
00:22:31,912 --> 00:22:33,292
Hi.

349
00:22:33,292 --> 00:22:35,740
What are you doing here?

350
00:22:36,372 --> 00:22:38,046
I was running an errand for my dad.

351
00:22:38,046 --> 00:22:40,171
[Woo General Hospital]

352
00:22:40,171 --> 00:22:41,856
This is your dad's hospital?

353
00:22:41,856 --> 00:22:43,441
Yeah.

354
00:22:44,731 --> 00:22:46,352
Why are you here?

355
00:22:46,352 --> 00:22:48,716
To shoot the sunset.

356
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:54,721
The patrol's coming soon.

357
00:22:54,721 --> 00:22:56,314
I should get going.

358
00:22:56,314 --> 00:22:58,320
You know the patrol schedule?

359
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,856
This is a great spot for night shots.

360
00:22:59,856 --> 00:23:01,694
I'm out.

361
00:23:01,694 --> 00:23:02,820
Wait up.

362
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:05,080
[Woo General Hospital]

363
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:12,982
But...

364
00:23:12,982 --> 00:23:15,581
- why are we hiding...
- Be quiet.

365
00:23:35,980 --> 00:23:38,316
Who's there?

366
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:40,179
Who's there?

367
00:23:40,179 --> 00:23:41,940
- Run!
- Huh?

368
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:43,439
Stop!

369
00:23:43,439 --> 00:23:45,342
I said stop!

370
00:23:47,907 --> 00:23:50,151
[Woo General Hospital]

371
00:24:36,439 --> 00:24:38,674
I'm exhausted.

372
00:24:47,564 --> 00:24:49,189
From now on,

373
00:24:49,189 --> 00:24:51,273
we're accomplices.

374
00:24:51,273 --> 00:24:53,188
Okay?

375
00:24:56,106 --> 00:24:57,624
Yeah.

376
00:25:13,273 --> 00:25:14,920
Let's go.

377
00:25:41,690 --> 00:25:43,827
I'll get off here.

378
00:25:43,827 --> 00:25:45,231
Here?

379
00:25:45,231 --> 00:25:47,743
I just want to walk a bit.

380
00:25:48,847 --> 00:25:50,823
Don't be late for class, and call me.

381
00:25:50,823 --> 00:25:52,221
Love you, son.

382
00:25:52,221 --> 00:25:54,041
Yeah, Mom.

383
00:26:03,023 --> 00:26:05,241
That's great, ma'am.

384
00:26:05,241 --> 00:26:08,506
Your face tells a story.

385
00:26:08,506 --> 00:26:10,414
So lonely.

386
00:26:10,414 --> 00:26:12,231
Great look,

387
00:26:12,231 --> 00:26:14,478
amazing light.

388
00:26:15,306 --> 00:26:17,856
Something's missing.

389
00:26:19,117 --> 00:26:20,596
Shadow.

390
00:26:20,596 --> 00:26:22,569
You scared me.

391
00:26:25,314 --> 00:26:29,070
What if there were some shadow on her face?

392
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:31,662
It'd look even lonelier.

393
00:26:41,815 --> 00:26:44,007
A little harder.

394
00:26:47,287 --> 00:26:50,089
No, what is this, a typhoon?

395
00:26:50,089 --> 00:26:52,849
Natural, keep it natural.

396
00:26:56,971 --> 00:26:57,847
[Mom]

397
00:26:57,847 --> 00:27:00,182
Soo Bin, focus.

398
00:27:00,182 --> 00:27:02,359
Yeah, sorry.

399
00:27:05,564 --> 00:27:07,567
Okay, that's perfect.

400
00:27:07,567 --> 00:27:09,449
Hold it.

401
00:27:12,267 --> 00:27:15,247
Who the hell are you? So loud.

402
00:27:15,247 --> 00:27:17,628
I can't sleep.

403
00:27:17,628 --> 00:27:19,835
Get the hell out.

404
00:27:21,273 --> 00:27:23,414
- That's my spot!
- Ma'am!

405
00:27:23,414 --> 00:27:25,228
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

406
00:27:25,228 --> 00:27:27,069
Hey, you need to apologize!

407
00:27:27,069 --> 00:27:30,648
This little brat, glaring at me?

408
00:27:30,648 --> 00:27:31,869
Do you know who I am?

409
00:27:31,869 --> 00:27:33,231
- Forget it! Let's just go!
- Huh?

410
00:27:33,231 --> 00:27:35,176
- It's fine.
- The cops will know.

411
00:27:35,176 --> 00:27:37,188
I got it all on camera!

412
00:27:37,188 --> 00:27:39,271
See you at the police station.

413
00:27:39,982 --> 00:27:42,983
Give it back!

414
00:27:44,606 --> 00:27:47,244
Now what?

415
00:27:47,244 --> 00:27:48,398
Hand it over.

416
00:27:48,398 --> 00:27:49,398
Let go.

417
00:27:49,398 --> 00:27:50,940
- Hand it over!
- Damn it.

418
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:53,070
You little shit, you.

419
00:27:53,070 --> 00:27:55,495
Do you know who I am?

420
00:27:58,523 --> 00:28:00,398
Give me the camera.

421
00:28:00,398 --> 00:28:02,078
You little shit!

422
00:28:02,078 --> 00:28:03,287
Stop it!

423
00:28:03,287 --> 00:28:04,585
I said stop!

424
00:28:04,585 --> 00:28:06,626
What?

425
00:28:06,626 --> 00:28:09,189
What the...

426
00:28:09,189 --> 00:28:11,231
I'll kill you, you shit.

427
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:12,481
Get me that camera.

428
00:28:12,481 --> 00:28:14,106
Over there!

429
00:28:14,106 --> 00:28:15,690
That guy is beating him up!

430
00:28:15,690 --> 00:28:18,094
Drunk in broad daylight, beating on a kid?

431
00:28:18,094 --> 00:28:20,564
- Come here.
- Still haven't learned?

432
00:28:20,564 --> 00:28:23,189
You okay, kid?

433
00:28:23,189 --> 00:28:25,856
You miserable shit, this is becoming a habit!

434
00:28:25,856 --> 00:28:27,944
Where the hell did he go?

435
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,547
You're tough. Really tough.

436
00:28:43,547 --> 00:28:46,608
Getting beaten up like that
and not making a sound.

437
00:28:47,564 --> 00:28:49,092
Sorry.

438
00:28:49,787 --> 00:28:50,927
It's fine.

439
00:28:50,927 --> 00:28:53,807
If it weren't for you,
that thing would've been ruined.

440
00:28:53,807 --> 00:28:55,231
But...

441
00:28:55,231 --> 00:28:57,412
it's still broken. That hurts.

442
00:29:08,856 --> 00:29:10,470
I...

443
00:29:11,147 --> 00:29:13,323
I'm going to like you.

444
00:29:16,273 --> 00:29:18,372
Is that okay with you?

445
00:29:21,314 --> 00:29:24,537
Not "I like you" but "I'm going to like you?"
What's that?

446
00:29:24,537 --> 00:29:25,828
I want to be like you.

447
00:29:25,828 --> 00:29:29,737
"I want to be like you?"
What's that supposed to mean?

448
00:29:29,737 --> 00:29:32,137
I've got pretty much everything.

449
00:29:32,137 --> 00:29:35,717
But there's one thing I don't have.

450
00:29:35,717 --> 00:29:37,633
Don't tell me...

451
00:29:37,633 --> 00:29:39,061
Me?

452
00:29:42,012 --> 00:29:43,427
A dream.

453
00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:49,221
You have one.

454
00:29:50,314 --> 00:29:54,114
That's what makes you shine.

455
00:29:56,484 --> 00:29:59,023
<i>Those words...</i>

456
00:29:59,023 --> 00:30:02,658
<i>to someone like me
who had nothing but a dream...</i>

457
00:30:02,658 --> 00:30:05,167
<i>were like a spell.</i>

458
00:30:08,079 --> 00:30:10,422
<i>It was my first love.</i>

459
00:30:28,643 --> 00:30:31,735
<i>Let's make a movie together.</i>

460
00:30:35,188 --> 00:30:36,794
<i>Just imagine it.</i>

461
00:30:36,794 --> 00:30:40,773
<i>Our names side by side in the credits.</i>

462
00:30:40,773 --> 00:30:44,289
<i>We'll do something great together.</i>

463
00:30:58,755 --> 00:31:00,356
<i>But that spell...</i>

464
00:31:00,356 --> 00:31:03,380
<i>soon turned into a curse.</i>

465
00:31:15,189 --> 00:31:16,609
Are you out of your mind?

466
00:31:16,609 --> 00:31:18,190
What the hell are you doing here?

467
00:31:18,190 --> 00:31:19,709
Isn't this a TV station?

468
00:31:19,709 --> 00:31:21,110
Why else would I come to a TV station?

469
00:31:21,110 --> 00:31:22,439
Is this a coincidence?

470
00:31:22,439 --> 00:31:24,250
- A coincidence?
- Want me to say it's not?

471
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,469
Hey!

472
00:31:25,469 --> 00:31:27,049
I was hoping I might see you.

473
00:31:27,049 --> 00:31:29,568
And seeing you... it's good.

474
00:31:29,568 --> 00:31:32,564
I missed you, Ju Yi Jae.

475
00:31:32,564 --> 00:31:35,757
- Did you not miss me?
- Bullshit.

476
00:31:36,402 --> 00:31:37,815
Still got that filthy mouth.

477
00:31:37,815 --> 00:31:39,670
Ain't nothing but rough memories...

478
00:31:39,670 --> 00:31:42,055
so I'm not sugarcoating it.

479
00:31:44,773 --> 00:31:46,023
What?

480
00:31:46,023 --> 00:31:48,061
What's going on?

481
00:31:49,982 --> 00:31:52,148
Anyone in there?

482
00:31:52,898 --> 00:31:55,819
- Get out of my face.
- You sure about that?

483
00:31:56,523 --> 00:31:58,383
It's not opening.

484
00:32:00,982 --> 00:32:02,314
Excuse me?

485
00:32:02,314 --> 00:32:03,696
It's not opening.

486
00:32:03,696 --> 00:32:05,189
Let's just take the elevator.

487
00:32:05,189 --> 00:32:06,997
Yeah, let's go.

488
00:32:10,690 --> 00:32:12,544
Move your hand.

489
00:32:13,184 --> 00:32:14,401
You got a boyfriend?

490
00:32:14,401 --> 00:32:15,940
Got a husband and a kid too.

491
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:17,081
What about it?

492
00:32:17,081 --> 00:32:18,294
So you don't.

493
00:32:18,294 --> 00:32:21,011
Got time, then?

494
00:32:22,481 --> 00:32:24,648
Oops.

495
00:32:24,648 --> 00:32:26,261
You said let go.

496
00:32:26,261 --> 00:32:28,310
Sorry. Let's grab lunch.

497
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:30,931
We're not exactly on lunch terms.

498
00:32:30,931 --> 00:32:34,899
- Side by side, then?
- I'm full. Had gukbap.

499
00:32:36,147 --> 00:32:39,523
Still funny as ever.

500
00:32:39,523 --> 00:32:41,774
Are you on some show or what?

501
00:32:41,774 --> 00:32:44,273
Going on about first love
and keeping promises...

502
00:32:44,273 --> 00:32:45,819
say any of that, and you're done.

503
00:32:45,819 --> 00:32:48,447
Korea's a small country.

504
00:32:48,447 --> 00:32:50,490
If I get doxxed, you taking the blame?

505
00:32:50,490 --> 00:32:52,749
So you've been keeping tabs on me.

506
00:32:52,749 --> 00:32:56,231
- I like that.
- Why are you stuck on that?

507
00:32:56,231 --> 00:32:57,375
Did you hate me a lot?

508
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:59,442
Yeah, cursed you every day.

509
00:32:59,442 --> 00:33:01,815
But I guess the universe isn't on my side.

510
00:33:01,815 --> 00:33:04,380
Seeing you become a director and all,

511
00:33:04,380 --> 00:33:06,806
I could die of jealousy.

512
00:33:09,023 --> 00:33:10,805
You promised.

513
00:33:10,805 --> 00:33:12,742
To become a director.

514
00:33:12,742 --> 00:33:16,149
That promise broke
when you left for the States.

515
00:33:19,773 --> 00:33:21,021
Anyway.

516
00:33:21,021 --> 00:33:23,482
Pull that "hey" stunt again
and something else breaks.

517
00:33:23,482 --> 00:33:25,234
Best if we don't run into each other.

518
00:33:25,234 --> 00:33:27,660
Just steer clear, okay?

519
00:33:28,731 --> 00:33:29,762
Geez.

520
00:33:29,762 --> 00:33:31,581
What?

521
00:33:34,147 --> 00:33:35,740
You know?

522
00:33:37,189 --> 00:33:40,041
You lost a lot of brain cells today.

523
00:33:40,041 --> 00:33:42,042
Go home and pat yourself on the back.

524
00:33:42,042 --> 00:33:43,342
What are you on about?

525
00:33:43,342 --> 00:33:44,481
Are you nuts?

526
00:33:44,481 --> 00:33:46,112
Move.

527
00:33:49,481 --> 00:33:52,052
Knew it.

528
00:33:52,052 --> 00:33:53,053
[Stairwell]

529
00:33:53,053 --> 00:33:55,183
Already gone?

530
00:34:06,606 --> 00:34:08,952
Come on.

531
00:34:10,189 --> 00:34:11,564
Chicken's here!

532
00:34:11,564 --> 00:34:13,665
Hey, set the table.

533
00:34:15,326 --> 00:34:17,585
Thanks.

534
00:34:30,189 --> 00:34:32,481
Why do you always eat chicken at my place?

535
00:34:32,481 --> 00:34:34,219
You think I'm buying because you're cute?

536
00:34:34,219 --> 00:34:36,674
It's the curse of living alone, jerk.

537
00:34:36,674 --> 00:34:37,854
Cheers.

538
00:34:37,854 --> 00:34:39,403
Cheers.

539
00:34:46,731 --> 00:34:48,658
So good.

540
00:34:50,982 --> 00:34:52,611
Hey.

541
00:34:52,611 --> 00:34:54,953
Who hand-delivers profiles these days?

542
00:34:54,953 --> 00:34:56,652
Just use an agency.

543
00:34:56,652 --> 00:34:58,661
And quit the delivery gig.

544
00:34:58,661 --> 00:35:01,999
Every bike I see, I think of you.

545
00:35:01,999 --> 00:35:03,731
Your dad worries too.

